---

<Layout title="Session 110 — Tales of the Radiant Citadel" description="Five weeks off the table, and the party picked up amid mountains of loose ends. They identified the Shield Bearer's sword (+1d6 radiant, +3d6 vs. undead/fi">
  <section class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 py-20">
    <a href="/studio" class="text-sm text-earth hover:text-ink transition-colors mb-6 inline-block">&larr; Studio</a>

    <h1 class="font-heading text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black leading-tight mb-2">
      Session 110
    </h1>
    <p class="text-sm text-earth mb-1">Tales of the Radiant Citadel &middot; April 14, 2026</p>
    <p class="text-sm text-ink-light mb-8">Post-Arc 8 — Crimson Rasp / Citadel Underworld → Blood Spur Expedition Prep</p>

    <div class="prose-section text-ink-light leading-relaxed mb-12 space-y-4">
      <p>
        Five weeks off the table, and the party picked up amid mountains of loose ends. They identified the Shield Bearer's sword (+1d6 radiant, +3d6 vs. undead/fiends, makes wielder leader of the Shield Bearers), then split. Toven, Kiet, and Virgil confronted Ed Zynka at the Second Chance Lounge to end the sewage blockade — the conversation collapsed into combat when Virgil grabbed her shoulder after she'd already agreed to shut it down. Ed Zynka deployed two tattoo-summoned shield guardians and a decapitated medusa head (&quot;Stan Medusa Head&quot;). Toven ended it with a casual Wall of Stone and a Matrix-style walkaway. Meanwhile Sundr and Haru met Commissar Lee at the Shield Bearer HQ — returned the sword, learned the full dark lore of the Lady in the Black Veil (glass-shattering presence, soul thief, cannot truly die), and secured a line on a concordant jewel via the La Mortia embassy. Sundr then visited the Sunweaver temple and cast Legend Lore (500 gold), receiving a direct vision: the lost world is called **Blood Spur**, a sunless mountainous wasteland with tunnels of rats carpeting the underground. The Sunweaver's directive: **&quot;Be the sun.&quot;** Toven negotiated with the cranium rats and secured a rat guide — **Twelve**, an ostracized individual from the hive mind who likes cheese. The party unanimously voted to pursue the Lost Civilization (Blood Spur) first, over God's Breath and Yanido. Sundr and Twelve combined the Legend Lore vision with ancestral rat memories to attune the concordant jewel — 85% confidence in locating Blood Spur. Kiet's ring, mollified, believes the wizard **Kenazaro** may be waiting at the other end.
      </p>
    </div>

    <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl font-bold mb-2">Highlights</h2>
    <ul class="text-sm text-ink-light leading-relaxed space-y-2 mb-12 list-disc list-inside">
      <li><strong class="text-ink">Five Weeks Later</strong> — Sam, welcoming Erik back: &quot;It has been a back. Yeah. Welcome back to us. It's amazing how long a month feels in D and D time.&quot;</li>
      <li><strong class="text-ink">Identifying the Shield Bearer's Sword</strong> — 10-minute ritual at the start of session — the sword had never actually been identified</li>
      <li><strong class="text-ink">The Second Chance Lounge — Confrontation with Ed Zynka</strong> — Toven, Kiet, and Virgil enter the bar. Sam: &quot;There's a number of people. Ed Zynka is behind the bar. Everything seems calm and normalish. As she looks up, you can see that she has rested her hand beneath the bar. She's ready for this to go south at least a little bit.&quot;</li>
      <li><strong class="text-ink">Ed Zynka Fight — Shield Guardians and Stan Medusa Head</strong> — Two tattoos on her arms flash — one red, one blue — and **two massive metal shield guardians** manifest on either side of her</li>
      <li><strong class="text-ink">Sundr &amp; Haru at the Shield Bearer HQ</strong> — Commissar Lee brings them back to his office. &quot;About as much activity as you've ever seen there. People arming and training and moving weapons and goods around.&quot;</li>
      <li><strong class="text-ink">The Lore of the Lady in the Black Veil</strong> — Lee drops the full dark version: &quot;She's when she's seen, she appears. She kills, glass shatters at the evil of her sight. Men perish immediately. And those who don't, she kills in other ways. She takes people's souls.&quot;</li>
      <li><strong class="text-ink">Sundr's Legend Lore at the Sunweaver Temple</strong> — Sundr visits the Sunweaver temple — gaudy, gold-plated, tourists with flashbulb cameras everywhere</li>
      <li><strong class="text-ink">The Cranium Rat Negotiation &amp; Twelve</strong> — Toven returns in rat form to the rat nexus via Speak with Animals</li>
      <li><strong class="text-ink">Quest Path Vote</strong> — Three options:</li>
      <li><strong class="text-ink">Attuning the Concordant Jewel</strong> — Lee delivers the jewel from La Mortia: &quot;Apparently, you people are some kind of heroes in the new government of La Mortia.&quot;</li>
      <li><strong class="text-ink">Kiet's Ring — Post-Credits Sting</strong> — After all the planning, Kiet's ring speaks: &quot;Kiet. So at long last, we are going to the wizard Kenazaro. Right? He might be here. We have no reason to think that he's not.&quot;</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl font-bold mb-6">Art</h2>
    <div class="space-y-10">
      {images.map((img) => (
        <figure>
          <img
            src={img.src}
            alt={img.title}
            class="w-full rounded-xl shadow-lg"
            loading="lazy"
          />
          <figcaption class="mt-3">
            <span class="font-semibold text-ink text-sm">{img.title}</span>
            <p class="text-sm text-ink-light mt-1">{img.caption}</p>
          </figcaption>
        </figure>
      ))}
    </div>

    <div class="border-t border-cream-dark mt-16 pt-8">
      <h2 class="font-heading text-xl font-bold mb-3">Party</h2>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-3 gap-4 text-sm">
        <div><span class="font-semibold text-ink">Sundr</span> <span class="text-ink-light">(Erik) — Aasimar Sorcerer</span></div>
        <div><span class="font-semibold text-ink">Kiet</span> <span class="text-ink-light">(Jonas) — Dragonborn Fighter</span></div>
        <div><span class="font-semibold text-ink">Virgil Gemnar</span> <span class="text-ink-light">(Kyle) — Goliath Barbarian</span></div>
        <div><span class="font-semibold text-ink">Toven</span> <span class="text-ink-light">(Max) — Druid</span></div>
        <div><span class="font-semibold text-ink">Haru</span> <span class="text-ink-light">(Hunter) — Kobold Paladin</span></div>
        <div><span class="font-semibold text-ink">—</span> <span class="text-ink-light">(Sam (DM))</span></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
